{
  "stem": "27507.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was-- there was Damka, who was my cousin who was then maybe 14 or 15, and was preparing for-- for her school exams, although I'm not quite sure what school, where she was doing it, if she was doing it all privately.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But I-- I enjoyed the atmosphere in [POLISH] because there were-- everybody was terribly full of-- of beans, so to say, and they were talking about many things and arguing and very lively.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And on the whole, they were always in good spirits, in spite of the situation being very unhappy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But they always were in good spirits and-- and full of talking and full of interest.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I stayed as well in another flat in [POLISH], I think, in a-- where-- of another uncle, another brother of my mother.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Joachim was his-- where he lived with his wife and with my cousin Rutka.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And there were there as well I think other members of that family.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "That was the family of-- of my uncle.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They were called Gesundheit and they lived there as well in the same flat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I think there were three families living in the flat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I think that was a large flat where only one family lived before the war and now there were probably three of them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And that was, of course, a common thing in ghetto, that if you had family which lived before the war somewhere else, maybe outside Warsaw and part of Warsaw which was then not in the ghetto, you had willy-nilly to accept that the family moved in with you, because there was absolutely--it would be unthinkable to do anything else.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I didn't mention as well that when the ghetto was started, that was, of course, surrounded-- in the very beginning, it was surrounded by the barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
